Former Transnet board member and Gupta family associate, Iqbal Sharma, has been denied bail. He faces charges of fraud and money laundering alongside several others including Free State Agriculture officials and the Guptas. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 BLOEMFONTEIN - Former Transnet board member and Gupta family associate, Iqbal Sharma, has been denied bail. He faces charges of fraud and money laundering alongside several others including Free State Agriculture officials and the Guptas. READ: Sharma continues with bail bid It is in connection with over R24.9 million the department paid for a 2011 feasibility study for the failed Estina dairy farm project. Three of Sharma's other co-accused have been granted bail. Watch the video above for more details on the story.